---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Band Saw Blades | Bi-Metal & Carbide-Tipped"
  description="High-performance industrial band saw blades. Bi-metal and carbide-tipped configurations for wood, metal, and specialty cutting applications."
>
  <section class="gradient-hero text-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6">Band Saw Blades</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100">
          Bi-metal and carbide-tipped band saw blades engineered for continuous industrial operation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose-custom">
        <h2>Industrial Band Saw Blade Solutions</h2>
        <p>
          Industrial band sawing requires a delicate balance between blade flexibility and cutting edge hardness. 
          Our bi-metal and carbide-tipped band saw blades withstand the extreme fatigue cycles of continuous 
          sawmill and metal fabrication operations.
        </p>

        <h3>Bi-Metal Blades</h3>
        <p>
          Bi-metal blades combine a flexible, fatigue-resistant spring steel back with high-speed steel teeth. 
          This construction provides exceptional durability for demanding applications.
        </p>
        
        <h4>Bi-Metal Advantages</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Flexible alloy backing resists breakage</li>
          <li>HSS teeth (M42 with 8% cobalt) for extended sharpness</li>
          <li>Ideal for contour cutting and resawing</li>
          <li>Cost-effective for general-purpose cutting</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Carbide-Tipped Band Saws</h3>
        <p>
          For extreme cutting conditions, carbide-tipped band saw blades provide unmatched wear resistance 
          and heat tolerance.
        </p>

        <h4>Carbide-Tipped Applications</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Hardwood resawing (high-silica content)</li>
          <li>Exotic and composite materials</li>
          <li>Metal cutting in production environments</li>
          <li>Frozen wood processing</li>
          <li>Abrasive materials (MDF, particleboard)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Tooth Patterns</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Standard Tooth</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">General-purpose cutting. Good for ferrous and non-ferrous metals, wood, and plastics.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Hook Tooth</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Aggressive feed rate. Ideal for wood, plastics, and non-ferrous metals. Large gullet for chip removal.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Skip Tooth</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Wider gullet spacing. Better chip clearance for softwoods and non-ferrous metals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Variable Pitch</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Mixed tooth spacing reduces vibration and noise. Excellent for interrupted cuts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Blade Width and Thickness</h3>
        <p>
          Blade width determines the minimum radius for contour cutting. Wider blades provide straighter 
          cuts in resaw applications.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Narrow (1/4" - 1/2"):</strong> Contour cutting, tight radii</li>
          <li><strong>Medium (3/4" - 1"):</strong> General purpose, balance of maneuverability and stability</li>
          <li><strong>Wide (1-1/4" - 2"):</strong> Resawing, straight cuts, maximum stability</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Tooth Pitch Selection</h3>
        <p>
          Select tooth pitch based on material thickness and type:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>2-3 TPI:</strong> Large sections, resawing, soft materials</li>
          <li><strong>4-6 TPI:</strong> General purpose, solid materials</li>
          <li><strong>8-14 TPI:</strong> Thin sections, tubing, sheet metal</li>
          <li><strong>Variable:</strong> Mixed materials, vibration reduction</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Welding and Repair</h3>
        <p>
          Our precision welding service creates seamless joints with proper annealing. We can also repair 
          damaged blades including tooth replacement and body straightening.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Need Band Saw Blades?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
        Custom widths, lengths, and tooth configurations available.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="bg-secondary text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary transition">
        Request Quote
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
